WEBVTT

00:11.315 --> 00:13.883
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT
IN THE TOWN OF COEUR d'LOUISE,

00:13.926 --> 00:18.061
YOUNG LILY CHARLES WAS 5 YEARS,
16 HOURS, AND 2 MINUTES OLD.

00:18.105 --> 00:20.020
3 DAYS EARLIER,
HER SISTER, VIVIAN,

00:20.063 --> 00:22.022
WAS BORN WITH
A HOLE IN HER HEART.

00:22.065 --> 00:25.547
CARDIOLOGISTS PATCHED THE FLAW,
AND LILY RECEIVED HER ORDERS --

00:25.590 --> 00:28.593
PUT HER VULNERABLE SIBLING
BEFORE HERSELF.

00:32.554 --> 00:33.946
ON HER 11th BIRTHDAY,

00:33.990 --> 00:36.384
LAND-LOVING LILY
WAS GIVEN A BACKYARD POOL

00:36.427 --> 00:39.343
AND A SWIMMING SUIT THAT MATCHED
HER SISTER VIVIAN'S.

00:39.387 --> 00:40.866
LILY WOULD SOON REALIZE

00:40.910 --> 00:43.260
THAT CONSTANT EXPOSURE
TO HER YOUNGER SISTER

00:43.304 --> 00:46.263
MADE VIVIAN A DEVOTED MIMIC.

00:49.397 --> 00:51.964
FROM MATCHING SWIMSUITS
AND BACKYARD "POOLERY,"

00:52.008 --> 00:54.054
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS
WERE BORN.

00:54.097 --> 00:56.099
THE RENOWNED
SYNCHRONIZED-SWIMMING SISTERS

00:56.143 --> 01:00.016
WERE LOYAL BEYOND SEPARATION
UNTIL CHARLES CHARLES.

01:00.060 --> 01:02.932
ENGAGED TO SISTER VIVIAN
BUT IN LOVE WITH SISTER LILY,

01:02.975 --> 01:06.109
CHARLES CHARLES NOT ONLY PLANTED
THE SEEDS OF BETRAYAL,

01:06.153 --> 01:07.763
HE SOWED THEM.

01:07.806 --> 01:10.505
SHAMED BY THE AFFAIR
WITH HER SISTER'S FIANCE,

01:10.548 --> 01:13.551
LILY JOINED THE SISTERS
OF THE DIVINE MAGNATUM,

01:13.595 --> 01:17.077
WHERE SHE HID HER LOVE CHILD
FROM VIVIAN AND THE WORLD.

01:17.120 --> 01:19.209
NO SOONER
WAS LILY'S LOVE CHILD BORN

01:19.253 --> 01:22.343
THAN LILY HAD TO GIVE HER UP
TO KEEP THE SECRET.

01:22.386 --> 01:25.520
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN LOSING
HER DAUGHTER AND LOSING HER EYE,

01:25.563 --> 01:27.696
LILY LOST THE WILL TO PERFORM.

01:27.739 --> 01:30.873
LILY'S DAUGHTER, CHARLOTTE,
WAS RAISED BY HER FATHER

01:30.916 --> 01:33.702
AND TOLD
HER MOTHER DIED GIVING BIRTH.

01:33.745 --> 01:35.399
WHEN CHARLOTTE'S FATHER DIED,

01:35.443 --> 01:37.532
HER MOTHER
CAME BACK INTO HER LIFE,

01:37.575 --> 01:40.317
BUT NOT AS HER MOTHER --
AS HER AUNT.

01:40.361 --> 01:44.016
INCAPACITATED BY THE LIES
SHE WAS FORCED TO KEEP TELLING,

01:44.060 --> 01:45.931
LILY RETREATED FROM THE WORLD

01:45.975 --> 01:48.630
AND TOOK VIVIAN AND CHARLOTTE
WITH HER.

01:48.673 --> 01:50.240
AND THEN CHARLOTTE DIED.

01:50.284 --> 01:51.676
AT THIS VERY MOMENT,

01:51.720 --> 01:54.114
LILY AND VIVIAN
WERE COMMEMORATING A BIRTHDAY --

01:54.157 --> 01:56.159
SPECIFICALLY, A HALF-BIRTHDAY --

01:56.203 --> 01:58.118
FOR THEIR NIECE/DAUGHTER,
CHARLOTTE,

01:58.161 --> 02:01.338
WHO PASSED AWAY
1 1/2 BIRTHDAYS AGO.

02:01.382 --> 02:03.819
SHE WAS
SUCH A HAPPY GIRL.

02:03.862 --> 02:05.255
IT'S AS IF
WHEN SHE DIED,

02:05.299 --> 02:07.779
THE MERRIMENT IN THIS HOME
DIED WITH HER.

02:07.823 --> 02:08.737
Lily: GOOD LORD.

02:08.780 --> 02:10.434
SORRY FOR BEING DISMAL.

02:10.478 --> 02:15.570
IT WOULD BE A RELIEF TO BE
AS STRONG AND STOIC AS YOU.

02:15.613 --> 02:17.572
DEAR ME.
THE AQUACADE IS IN TOWN.

02:17.615 --> 02:19.835
REMEMBER TAKING CHARLOTTE THERE
FOR HER HALF-BIRTHDAYS?

02:19.878 --> 02:22.925
IT'S AS IF AN ANGEL
CALLED THE PAPEN COUNTY PICAYUNE

02:22.968 --> 02:25.057
AND PLACED AN AD
ON THE BACK PAGE.

02:25.101 --> 02:28.148
ARE YOU DONE GAWKING?
BIRDCAGES NEED FRESH LINERS.

02:28.191 --> 02:30.933
LILY,
LET'S GO TO THE AQUACADE.

02:30.976 --> 02:33.065
IT COULD BE JUST THE THING
TO HELP THE GLOOM PASS.

02:33.109 --> 02:34.110
PLEASE.

02:34.154 --> 02:35.894
FOR ME?

02:35.938 --> 02:38.723
Narrator: THOUGH LILY WAS
WEAK WITH GRIEF, HER COMPULSION

02:38.767 --> 02:41.509
TO PUT HER SISTER'S HAPPINESS
BEFORE HER OWN

02:41.552 --> 02:42.771
DROVE HER TO SAY...

02:42.814 --> 02:44.207
FIND MY OPERA GLOVES.

02:44.251 --> 02:47.210
ALL THOSE CHILDREN,
TOURISTS IN CULOTTES --

02:47.254 --> 02:49.604
PLACE WILL BE
CRAWLING WITH GERMS.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.823
Narrator:
AND SO VIVIAN MADE A WISH.

02:52.607 --> 02:54.086
[ BLOWS ]

02:54.130 --> 02:56.698
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU REMEMBERED MY HALF-BIRTHDAY.

02:56.741 --> 02:57.960
HOW COULD WE FORGET?

02:58.003 --> 03:00.223
WITH YOU
NEVER SHUTTING UP ABOUT IT.

03:00.267 --> 03:02.051
HERE'S A LITTLE SOMETHING
FROM ME.

03:02.094 --> 03:03.922
A FIRST EDITION.

03:03.966 --> 03:05.054
OH, AND IT'S SIGNED
BY THE AUTHOR!

03:05.097 --> 03:06.621
THANK YOU, EMERSON.

03:06.664 --> 03:09.537
NOW, WHERE'S YOURS,
BOYFRIEND OF HALF-BIRTHDAY GIRL?

03:09.580 --> 03:11.800
NED THINKS HE'S A TERRIBLE
GIFT-GIVER.I AM.

03:11.843 --> 03:12.888
HE GETS OBSESSED WITH
FINDING THE PERFECT GIFT

03:12.931 --> 03:14.237
THAT DOESN'T EXIST.

03:14.281 --> 03:15.934
IT DOES.AND THEN
HE PSYCHS HIMSELF OUT

03:15.978 --> 03:18.067
TO THE POINT WHERE
HE DOESN'T GIFT ANYTHING.

03:18.110 --> 03:21.201
BUT HE'S ALREADY GIVEN ME THE
GREATEST GIFT OF ALL --
MY LIFE BACK.

03:21.244 --> 03:23.681
STILL, I'M NOT GIVING UP
FINDING THE PERFECT GIFT.

03:24.987 --> 03:26.423
WHAT DIED?

03:26.467 --> 03:28.295
COUPLE DOZEN MINKS,
GIVE OR TAKE.

03:28.338 --> 03:31.123
LILY ASKED ME TO TAKE THEM
TO THE FURRIER FOR A FLUFFING.

03:31.167 --> 03:32.603
SHE AND VIVIAN ARE GOING
TO THE AQUACADE TONIGHT

03:32.647 --> 03:33.996
TO CELEBRATE
CHUCK'S HALF-BIRTHDAY.

03:34.039 --> 03:36.346
I'M SO TOUCHED!
AREN'T YOU TOUCHED, NED?

03:36.390 --> 03:38.000
I'M NOT SURE.
WHAT'S AN AQUACADE?

03:38.043 --> 03:39.784
IT'S, LIKE,
THIS TRAVELING WATER SHOW,

03:39.828 --> 03:43.005
AND YOU HAVE DIVERS AND SWIMMERS
AND BREATHTAKING DAREDEVILS.

03:43.048 --> 03:44.485
IT ALWAYS CAME TO TOWN
THE MONTH OF MY HALF-BIRTHDAY,

03:44.528 --> 03:45.834
AND LILY, VIVIAN, AND I
WOULD ALWAYS GO.

03:45.877 --> 03:47.749
THAT'S IT!
MY PERFECT GIFT!

03:47.792 --> 03:50.012
I'M GONNA BUY SIX TICKETS
TO THE AQUACADE.

03:50.055 --> 03:52.057
EMERSON, CALL SIMONE.
IN WITH THE FLU.

03:52.101 --> 03:52.971
OLIVE, CALL RANDY.

03:53.015 --> 03:54.059
OUT WITH THE GOUT.

03:54.103 --> 03:56.758
SO, FOUR TICKETS
TO THE AQUACADE.

03:56.801 --> 03:58.325
OHH! DOUBLE DATE!
DOUBLE DATE!

03:58.368 --> 04:00.457
[ TROPICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

04:03.678 --> 04:05.462
PREPARE TO BE AMAZED.

04:05.506 --> 04:07.899
THERE HAS NOT BEEN THIS MUCH
TALENT AROUND A BODY OF WATER

04:07.943 --> 04:10.032
SINCE MOSES
PLAYED THE RED SEA.

04:10.075 --> 04:12.339
LOOK -- FIRST,
MASTER OF CEREMONIES AND SONG,

04:12.382 --> 04:13.992
JIMMY NEPTUNE.OOH!

04:14.036 --> 04:15.864
SOLO-SYNCH SENSATION
SID TANGO.

04:15.907 --> 04:17.213
YEAH!

04:17.257 --> 04:18.823
SHARK RIDER GALVESTON GUS

04:18.867 --> 04:20.521
AND HIS DORSAL-FINNED FRIEND
BUBBA!

04:20.564 --> 04:22.262
AND YOUR AUNTS.

04:22.305 --> 04:23.611
OH!

04:27.049 --> 04:29.007
[ LAUGHS ]

04:32.010 --> 04:34.883
Chuck: THEY'RE THE SERENA
AND VENUS OF WATER BALLET,
AND NO ONE'S LOOKING?

04:34.926 --> 04:36.580
NO ONE'S EVEN NOT LOOKING
THE WAY YOU PRETEND

04:36.624 --> 04:38.060
NOT TO LOOK
WHEN YOU'RE ACTUALLY LOOKING.

04:38.103 --> 04:39.061
Narrator:
BUT SOMEONE WAS.

04:39.104 --> 04:41.324
HOOYAH.HOOYAH.

04:41.368 --> 04:42.586
THE DARLING
MERMAID DARLINGS.THE DARLING
MERMAID DARLINGS.

04:42.630 --> 04:44.109
LOOK -- FANS!

04:44.153 --> 04:46.503
NO, THEY ARE NOT FANS.
THEY'RE THE AQUADOLLS.

04:46.547 --> 04:48.113
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

04:48.157 --> 04:51.116
BLANCHE AND CORAL RAMORA,
A.K.A. THE AQUADOLLS,

04:51.160 --> 04:53.118
SHAPED THEIR ACT
INTO A SWIMMING CELEBRATION

04:53.162 --> 04:54.946
OF THE RED, WHITE, AND BLUE.

04:54.990 --> 04:58.080
BUT THE AQUADOLLS WEREN'T THE
ONLY SYNCHRONIZED-SISTER DUO.

04:58.123 --> 05:00.300
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS
WERE, TOO,

05:00.343 --> 05:02.476
AND THUS GREW A BITTER RIVALRY.

05:02.519 --> 05:04.042
WHAT HAS YOU TWO
CHUMMING THE WATERS?

05:04.086 --> 05:05.957
I COULD ASK THE SAME,
CHUM.

05:06.001 --> 05:08.786
OH, THE CHARLES SISTERS,
STILL OUT OF THE LOOP --

05:08.830 --> 05:09.787
HOW QUAINT
AND REFRESHING.

05:09.831 --> 05:11.267
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

05:11.311 --> 05:13.356
WE'RE TONIGHT'S HEADLINERS.
DIDN'T YOU KNOW?

05:14.357 --> 05:15.880
YO, DOLLS.

05:15.924 --> 05:18.535
OH, THIS IS OUR MANAGER --
UH, BLANCHE'S HUSBAND.

05:18.579 --> 05:21.059
INSATIABLE HUSBAND --
SHANE TRICKLE.

05:21.103 --> 05:23.366
I FOUND HIM WHEN WE WERE
PERFORMING IN HONOLULU.

05:24.019 --> 05:25.368
HAWAII.

05:25.412 --> 05:27.588
SHAKE TAIL. CURTAIN'S IN 20.
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:27.631 --> 05:29.720
WELL, OFF TO DO
WHAT WE DO BEST --

05:29.764 --> 05:31.635
SWIM
FOR CHRIST AND COUNTRY.

05:31.679 --> 05:33.681
MIGHT WANT
TO PICK A NEW FLAG --

05:33.724 --> 05:35.552
ONE WITHOUT
HORIZONTAL STRIPES.

05:35.596 --> 05:36.988
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:37.032 --> 05:39.034
YOU KNOW, IT'S A SHAME,
CUTTING THIS SHORT.

05:39.077 --> 05:41.166
WHY DON'T WE MEET
IN OUR DRESSING ROOM --

05:41.210 --> 05:43.517
LAVISH DRESSING ROOM
AFTER THE SHOW?

05:43.560 --> 05:44.996
THAT IS,
IF THE SHUTTLE BUS

05:45.040 --> 05:47.564
ISN'T IN A HURRY
TO GET YOU BACK TO THE HOME.

05:47.608 --> 05:49.087
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

05:54.571 --> 05:56.617
THIS WAS
AN UNANTICIPATED STRESSOR.

05:56.660 --> 05:58.227
I WOULD LIKE TO GO.

05:58.270 --> 05:59.707
VIVIAN!

05:59.750 --> 06:01.839
DO YOU THINK
I WANTED TO DRIVE 20 MILES

06:01.883 --> 06:03.798
TO A FAMILY-FRIENDLY
VENUE

06:03.841 --> 06:06.278
WITH ITS GENERAL-ADMISSION
PARKING LOT?

06:06.322 --> 06:08.411
THEY DON'T EVEN
SERVE ALCOHOL HERE.

06:08.455 --> 06:11.066
OH, MY GOODNESS.
YOU NEED TO SIT DOWN AT HOME?

06:11.109 --> 06:12.284
NO.

06:12.328 --> 06:14.591
WE ARE GONNA STAND UP.

06:14.635 --> 06:17.072
NOW, COME ON.
THIS IS CHARLOTTE'S CELEBRATION.

06:17.115 --> 06:18.682
HER MEMORY COMES FIRST.

06:18.726 --> 06:21.250
NOW, GET OUT YOUR TICKET.
WE'RE WADING IN.

06:21.293 --> 06:22.860
[ WHIMPERS ]

06:28.649 --> 06:30.433
[ SCOFFS ]

06:30.477 --> 06:33.175
DO THEY LOOK RATTLED?

06:33.218 --> 06:34.959
THE AQUADOLLS
IS THE WORST THING THAT COULD
HAVE HAPPENED TO THEM.

06:35.003 --> 06:36.396
I'M GONNA
HAVE TO SNEAK CLOSER

06:36.439 --> 06:37.701
AND SEE HOW THEY'RE DEALING
WITH EVERYTHING.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.703
MNH-MNH-MNH-MNH-MNH.

06:42.489 --> 06:44.839
OH, THE COTTON-CANDY VENDOR
IS A VERY LARGE MAN

06:44.882 --> 06:48.016
WITH A DOUBLY LARGE DISPLAY
OF SPUN CANDY TO HIDE BEHIND.

06:48.059 --> 06:49.670
CHUCK.

06:49.713 --> 06:51.236
WELL, I HAVE TO DO SOMETHING,
AND WHAT CAN I DO

06:51.280 --> 06:52.455
FROM ALL THE WAY
BACK UP HERE?

06:52.499 --> 06:53.978
[ GASPS ]
I KNOW!

06:54.022 --> 06:55.806
LET'S LIFT THEIR SPIRITS
WITH AN AUNT CHANT.

06:55.850 --> 06:58.069
OR THE WAVE. IT'S NEVER BEEN
MORE APPROPRIATE.

06:58.113 --> 07:00.420
EMERSON, YOU START.

07:00.463 --> 07:02.117
OR SOMETHING
MORE TO THE POINT.

07:03.031 --> 07:05.076
SCREW THE AQUADOLLS!

07:08.689 --> 07:09.646
YAY!

07:09.690 --> 07:10.821
I GOT A SMILE.

07:10.865 --> 07:12.519
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

07:15.652 --> 07:18.960
GREETINGS, LADIES AND GENTS!

07:19.003 --> 07:22.616
WELCOME TO
MY "NIGHT OF 1,000 BUBBLES"!

07:22.659 --> 07:24.139
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE
CONTINUES ]

07:25.532 --> 07:27.795
IS THIS A FROTHY CROWD OR WHAT?

07:29.405 --> 07:30.841
BUBBA THE SHARK THINKS SO.

07:30.885 --> 07:32.495
[ CROWD "OOHs" ]

07:32.539 --> 07:33.670
MORE FROM HIM LATER.

07:33.714 --> 07:35.455
THANKS
FOR INSISTING WE STAY.

07:35.498 --> 07:37.500
NOW THE TASK
IS STAYING STRONG.

07:37.544 --> 07:42.505
BUT RIGHT NOW, LET US RISE
FOR OUR NATIONAL ANTHEM,

07:42.549 --> 07:46.770
AS INTERPRETED
BY THOSE PATRIOTIC PADDLERS,

07:46.814 --> 07:48.380
THE AQUADOLLS.

07:48.424 --> 07:49.817
[ CHEERING ]

07:51.558 --> 07:54.386
[ "THE STAR-SPANGLED BANNER"
PLAYS ]

07:59.566 --> 08:03.874
♪ OH, SAY, CAN YOU SEE

08:03.918 --> 08:05.615
THESE LADIES SWIM?!

08:10.272 --> 08:12.709
ESTHER WILLIAMS
WOULD PISS HER COTTON PANEL

08:12.753 --> 08:13.841
AT THE SIGHT
OF THOSE ROCKET SPLITS.

08:13.884 --> 08:15.669
[ CHUCKLES ]
LILY, BEHAVE.

08:15.712 --> 08:19.107
THOUGH I WILL ADMIT, BLANCHE
IS LOOKING LESS THAN BUOYANT.

08:20.891 --> 08:22.806
ARE YOU KIDDING?
SHE'S DEAD IN THE WATER.

08:22.850 --> 08:24.112
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:31.423 --> 08:32.642
[ CHOMP! ]

08:32.686 --> 08:33.817
AAH!
OHH!

08:33.861 --> 08:35.515
[ CROWD GASPS ]

08:42.478 --> 08:45.394
I MUST PEN A SYMPATHY NOTE
TO CORAL RAMORA.

08:45.437 --> 08:46.917
DON'T SIGN MY NAME
TO THAT

08:46.961 --> 08:49.833
"SORRY A SHARK ATE
YOUR BITCH OF A SISTER" LETTER.

08:49.877 --> 08:51.705
SHE WOULDN'T THINK TWICE
IF IT HAPPENED TO US.

08:51.748 --> 08:54.708
BUT TO HAVE A SISTER DIE.

08:54.751 --> 08:57.537
I DON'T KNOW HOW I'D SURVIVE
IF I'D LOST YOU.

08:57.580 --> 08:58.799
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

08:58.842 --> 09:02.063
WHO THE HELL IS THAT?

09:02.106 --> 09:04.456
VIVIAN CHARLES
OF THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS.

09:04.500 --> 09:07.024
TAILS, SCALES, AND ALL.

09:07.068 --> 09:09.026
I OVERHEARD
YOUR VERBAL SKIRMISH

09:09.070 --> 09:11.072
WITH THE AQUADOLLS
LAST NIGHT.

09:11.115 --> 09:12.377
HOPED TO GRAB YOU
AFTER THE SHOW,

09:12.421 --> 09:14.597
BUT IT SEEMED
THAT YOU WERE SWEPT AWAY

09:14.641 --> 09:16.425
BY THE...DEPARTING CROWD.

09:16.468 --> 09:19.036
WE SMALL-BONED PERSONS
ARE VULNERABLE

09:19.080 --> 09:22.387
TO EXODUSES OF THE MASS
AND PANICKED VARIETY.

09:22.431 --> 09:24.607
WE ALL THOUGHT
THE CHARLES SISTERS

09:24.651 --> 09:27.610
HAD GONE THE WAY OF LEGEND,
BUT, UH, GEE WHIZ,

09:27.654 --> 09:29.046
WHAT A TIME FOR A COMEBACK!

09:29.090 --> 09:31.135
COME AGAIN?

09:31.179 --> 09:33.485
MY FATHER OWNED THE AQUACADE
BEFORE ME,

09:33.529 --> 09:35.618
HIS FATHER BEFORE HIM.

09:35.662 --> 09:37.054
THAT'S HOW I KNOW
SAM NEPTUNE

09:37.098 --> 09:39.013
GAVE THE DARLINGS
THEIR FIRST BREAK.

09:39.056 --> 09:41.319
AS A BOY,
I WATCHED YOUR SET

09:41.363 --> 09:42.669
FROM THE WATER WINGS
EVERY NIGHT,

09:42.712 --> 09:44.409
AND I NEVER FORGOT
THE LOOK OF THE AUDIENCE

09:44.453 --> 09:45.846
AS THEY SOAKED IT IN.

09:45.889 --> 09:47.848
YOU TWO HAVE A GIFT
UNLIKE ANY I'VE SEEN.

09:47.891 --> 09:49.458
YOUR SWIMMING
BRINGS PEOPLE JOY.

09:49.501 --> 09:51.678
OUR SWIMMING BRINGS --

09:51.721 --> 09:53.288
BROUGHT US JOY, TOO.

09:53.331 --> 09:55.725
I'M IN DESPERATE NEED
OF A NEW OPENING ACT.

09:55.769 --> 09:58.075
COME BACK TO THE POOL,
MERMAIDS!

09:58.119 --> 10:00.948
AFTER A 24-HOUR MOURNING PERIOD
FOR POOR BLANCHE, OF COURSE.

10:02.340 --> 10:04.255
THE WATER'S NICE.WE'RE RETIRED.

10:04.299 --> 10:06.693
PEOPLE COME OUT OF RETIREMENT
ALL THE TIME.

10:06.736 --> 10:09.391
FOR HOW MANY PERFORMANCES
WOULD YOU WANT US?

10:09.434 --> 10:11.785
WHAT HAS GOTTEN INTO
YOUR GILL?

10:11.828 --> 10:13.221
WE HAD OUR TIME.

10:13.264 --> 10:15.876
AND HERE IT IS,
BACK AGAIN.

10:15.919 --> 10:17.268
WELL?

10:17.312 --> 10:18.574
ARE WE SWIMMIN', WOMEN?

10:20.402 --> 10:22.230
SAVE IT.
WE'RE IN TRAINING.

10:24.667 --> 10:25.973
OHH!
[ LAUGHS ]

10:32.936 --> 10:34.808
Gus:
DO I SMELL A FISHWICH?

10:34.851 --> 10:35.722
YES.

10:35.765 --> 10:37.593
YOU MIND
STOWING IT AWAY?

10:37.637 --> 10:38.638
YES.

10:40.248 --> 10:41.641
OH-HO.

10:46.863 --> 10:48.386
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

10:48.430 --> 10:49.692
ALL CLEAR.

10:53.043 --> 10:54.610
SORRY TO INCONVENIENCE,

10:54.654 --> 10:58.701
BUT THE SCENT OF FRIED FLOUNDER
TAKES ME BACK TO...

10:58.745 --> 10:59.963
MY RECENT LOSS.

11:00.007 --> 11:02.400
YOU COME HIGHLY RECOMMENDED,
MR. COD.

11:02.444 --> 11:04.446
THE NAME'S...GALVESTON GUS. YEAH, I KNOW.

11:04.489 --> 11:06.535
I ASSUME YOUR RECENT LOSS
IS BUBBA THE SHARK?

11:06.578 --> 11:08.363
YOU HEARD?I WAS THERE.

11:08.406 --> 11:10.931
WELL, I HOPE YOU AIN'T PART OF
THE NEGLIGENCE SUIT AGAINST ME.

11:10.974 --> 11:13.411
THEM LAWYERS
WANT TO TAKE EVERYTHING I HAVE.

11:13.455 --> 11:14.848
AND THAT'S
WHY I NEED YOU --

11:14.891 --> 11:17.154
TO PROVE
I WASN'T ASLEEP IN THE SADDLE.

11:17.198 --> 11:18.678
NOT MUCH I CAN DO.

11:18.721 --> 11:20.375
300 PEOPLE
SAW YOUR GREAT WHITE

11:20.418 --> 11:22.551
MAKE FISH FOOD OUT OF THAT
UNFORTUNATE WATER-HOOFER.

11:22.594 --> 11:25.510
I KNOW YOU CAN'T PROVE
BUBBA DIDN'T EAT MS. RAMORA.

11:25.554 --> 11:27.034
HE DID.

11:27.077 --> 11:30.124
AND WHAT A CRAP LAST MEAL
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN.

11:30.167 --> 11:32.561
BUT YOU CAN PROVE
SOMEONE ELSE AT THE AQUACADE

11:32.604 --> 11:35.390
LET HIM OUT OF HIS PEN AND
CAUSED THIS HORRIBLE ACCIDENT.

11:35.433 --> 11:36.913
WHAT'S GOT YOU
FLOATING THAT THEORY?

11:36.957 --> 11:38.959
I TRIPLE-CHECK
THE GATE OF HIS PADDOCK

11:39.002 --> 11:40.395
BEFORE EVERY PERFORMANCE.

11:42.484 --> 11:44.181
THIS HERE
IS THE ONLY WAY TO OPEN IT,

11:44.225 --> 11:47.010
AND IT NEVER LEAVES MY PERSON.
NO, SIR.

11:47.054 --> 11:51.362
SOMEONE ELSE OPENED HIS PEN
AND SET ME AND MY BOY UP.

11:51.406 --> 11:54.148
MR. COD,
BUBBA WAS MY BEST FRIEND

11:54.191 --> 11:57.020
EVER SINCE
HE WAS A GUPPY OF A PUP.

11:57.064 --> 11:59.544
AND THE ONLY HAPPINESS
I WILL GET FROM THIS MESS

11:59.588 --> 12:01.329
IS KNOWING
HIS GOOD NAME IS CLEAR.

12:01.372 --> 12:02.678
SO, PLEASE...

12:04.636 --> 12:06.421
...HELP
A SENTIMENTAL COWPOKE OUT.

12:09.554 --> 12:12.601
IN THIRD GRADE,
I DID A REPORT ON GREAT WHITES.

12:12.644 --> 12:14.037
DISCOVERED
WE WERE A LOT ALIKE,

12:14.081 --> 12:16.344
SEEING AS HOW WE'RE BOTH
MISUNDERSTOOD BADASSES.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.956
WELL, THIS MAY BE
A LONG SHOT, BUT...

12:20.000 --> 12:22.393
LET'S GIVE THE BIG FISH
A FAIR SHAKE.

12:22.437 --> 12:23.612
[ GROANS ]

12:23.655 --> 12:25.570
OOH.

12:25.614 --> 12:27.398
AAH!
OH!

12:29.009 --> 12:31.054
[ GRUNTS ]

12:31.098 --> 12:32.882
[ WATCH TICKING ]

12:32.926 --> 12:34.362
MS. RAMORA,
I'M SORRY TO INFORM YOU,

12:34.405 --> 12:36.277
BUT YOU'VE BEEN EATEN
BY BUBBA THE SHARK.

12:36.320 --> 12:37.713
DID EVERYBODY CRY?

12:37.757 --> 12:39.497
OH, OF COURSE THEY DID.
I'M THE FAN FAVE.

12:39.541 --> 12:41.891
DID YOU NOTICE
ANYTHING STRANGE BEFORE...

12:41.935 --> 12:43.371
[ HUMS "JAWS" THEME ]

12:43.414 --> 12:46.069
YES. MY SISTER ASKED ME
IF I WAS GOING GRAY.

12:46.113 --> 12:47.070
HOW ABOUT
SOMETHING PERTINENT?

12:47.114 --> 12:48.376
OH, FOR ME, IT'S STRANGE.

12:48.419 --> 12:50.421
MY MOTHER WAS AUBURN
TILL THE END.

12:50.465 --> 12:53.207
ONLY OTHER THING THAT CAN
BRING ON GRAY HAIR IS STRESS,

12:53.250 --> 12:54.730
AND MY HUSBAND, SHANE,

12:54.774 --> 12:56.906
IS THE BIGGEST STRESS-RELIEVER
I KNOW.

12:57.820 --> 12:59.561
BIG-GEST.

12:59.604 --> 13:01.345
ACTUALLY, I CAN SEE
SOMETHING WHITE IN THERE,

13:01.389 --> 13:02.390
BUT I DON'T THINK
IT'S HAIR.

13:02.433 --> 13:03.521
THAT'S MY HAIR GEL.

13:03.565 --> 13:05.697
YOU SURE
THAT AIN'T SHARK SLIME?

13:05.741 --> 13:07.569
WATER BALLERINAS
USE A VERY THICK HAIR GEL.

13:07.612 --> 13:09.353
IT'S WATERPROOF TO KEEP
THEIR HAIRSTYLES IN PLACE.

13:09.397 --> 13:10.572
IT'S KIND OF LIKE
SHELLAC.

13:10.615 --> 13:12.008
SHELLAC
WITH A FAINT SCENT OF...

13:12.052 --> 13:13.401
[ SNIFFS ] LARD.

13:13.444 --> 13:15.751
IT'S USED ALL THE TIME
IN PIE CRUSTS.

13:15.795 --> 13:18.580
WHY WOULD SOMEONE
PUT PIG FAT IN HER HAIR GEL?

13:18.623 --> 13:20.016
SHARKS CAN SMELL A DROP OF BLOOD
IN THE WATER

13:20.060 --> 13:21.757
A QUARTER-MILE AWAY.

13:21.801 --> 13:24.281
LARD SURE AS HELL WOULD HAVE
PROMPTED BUBBA TO STRIKE.

13:24.325 --> 13:25.979
ALL SOMEONE WOULD HAVE TO DO
IS OPEN THE PEN...

13:26.022 --> 13:28.459
AND WE GOT BONA FIDE
MURDER BY GREAT WHITE.

13:28.503 --> 13:32.115
WAIT --
LILY AND VIVIAN CHARLES.

13:32.159 --> 13:34.422
I KNEW THERE WAS A REASON
THEY WOULD COME OUT OF SECLUSION

13:34.465 --> 13:36.163
AFTER ALL THESE YEARS.

13:36.206 --> 13:38.600
SHREWS --
ALWAYS AFTER OUR LIMELIGHT.

13:38.643 --> 13:39.949
YOUR LIMELIGHT?
YOU WERE NOTHING

13:39.993 --> 13:41.559
BEFORE THE
DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS!

13:41.603 --> 13:43.910
THEY PUT SIBLING
SYNCHRO SWIMDANCE ON THE MAP!

13:43.953 --> 13:44.780
WHO ARE YOU?

13:44.824 --> 13:46.042
CHARLOTTE CHARLES --

13:46.086 --> 13:47.914
NIECE OF VIVIAN,
DAUGHTER OF LILY.

13:47.957 --> 13:49.567
NOW,
YOU HURT THEIR FEELINGS

13:49.611 --> 13:51.352
ON A NIGHT THEY WERE FEELING
VERY, VERY FRAGILE.

13:51.395 --> 13:53.702
SO YOU CAN JUST SHUT UP
ABOUT MY FAMILY,

13:53.745 --> 13:54.921
BLANCHE RAMORA-TRICKLE,

13:54.964 --> 13:56.923
OR YOU'LL END UP...

13:56.966 --> 13:59.577
WELL, I CA-- I CAN'T THINK
OF ANYTHING WORSE THAN HERE,

13:59.621 --> 14:01.405
SO...SNAP!

14:01.449 --> 14:03.364
NOW TOUCH HER! TOUCH HER!
TOUCH HER BEFORE SHE TALKS BACK!

14:03.407 --> 14:04.626
TOUCH HER! TOUCH HER!
TOUCH HER!

14:04.669 --> 14:06.280
HA HA!

14:06.323 --> 14:07.672
THAT FELT SO GOOD!

14:14.636 --> 14:16.681
THAT HAPLESS SHARK
WAS JUST A PATSY?

14:16.725 --> 14:18.466
Chuck: HE GOT A WHIFF OF
THE LARD THAT WAS MIXED

14:18.509 --> 14:20.468
INTO BLANCHE'S HAIR GEL AND THEN
JUST FOLLOWED HIS INSTINCTS.

14:20.511 --> 14:21.599
THE KILLER WOULD HAVE
NEEDED ACCESS

14:21.643 --> 14:22.992
TO THE
AQUADOLLS' DRESSING ROOM

14:23.036 --> 14:24.298
AND THE REMOTE
FOR THE SHARK GATE,

14:24.341 --> 14:26.126
ALL OF WHICH HOLLERS
"INSIDE JOB."

14:26.169 --> 14:27.823
SUDDENLY, OUR SWEET AQUACADE
LOOKS NASTIER

14:27.867 --> 14:29.259
THAN A BACKED-UP SINK
ON THANKSGIVING.

14:29.303 --> 14:31.044
THERE'S NO WAY OUR BAD FISH
IS GONNA NIBBLE

14:31.087 --> 14:33.481
WITH A BUNCH OF P.I.s
COMING TROLLING FOR MURDERERS.

14:33.524 --> 14:35.657
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT WE NEED NOW IS A COVER.

14:36.963 --> 14:38.094
MY AUNTS!

14:38.138 --> 14:39.182
LILY, VIVIAN.
A BOOTH? PIE?

14:39.226 --> 14:40.792
PIE AND BOOTH?

14:40.836 --> 14:43.970
Both: PERHAPS A SUGAR-FREE
APRICOT CUSTARD TO GO.

14:44.013 --> 14:47.364
WOW. YOU ALL ARE REALLY...
COORDINATED TODAY.

14:47.408 --> 14:51.978
OLIVE, WE'D LIKE BACK THE
DARLING MERMAID DARLING COSTUMES

14:52.021 --> 14:53.805
WE GAVE YOU
SOME TIME AGO.

14:53.849 --> 14:55.633
FEELING NOSTALGIC?NO.

14:55.677 --> 14:57.331
WE'RE JOINING
THE FLOATING CAST

14:57.374 --> 14:59.942
OF JIMMY NEPTUNE'S
"NIGHT OF 1,000 BUBBLES."

14:59.986 --> 15:02.727
THIS IS OUR
LIVING-IN-SYNC PRACTICE HOUR.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.077
O-M-G!

15:04.860 --> 15:06.209
G-R-8!

15:06.253 --> 15:07.167
T-T-F-N.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.995
NO -- B-R-B.

15:09.038 --> 15:11.867
SHE GOT A CASE
OF THE DUMB A-S-S.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.087
HOW ABOUT YOU TAKE A SEAT
FAR OVER THERE,

15:14.130 --> 15:15.653
WHERE YOU CAN, UM...

15:15.697 --> 15:17.742
DO -- DO WHATEVER IT IS
YOU'RE DOING.

15:20.006 --> 15:21.094
SWISH!SWISH!

15:21.137 --> 15:22.530
UH...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:22.573 --> 15:25.272
WELL, LADIES,
IF IT ISN'T A SMALL...SEA.

15:25.315 --> 15:26.969
UM, IT JUST SO HAPPENS

15:27.013 --> 15:29.406
I HAVE BUSINESS
AT JIMMY NEPTUNE'S, MYSELF.

15:29.450 --> 15:32.409
UH, WOULD YOU MIND STEPPING
OUTSIDE FOR A LITTLE CHAT?

15:32.453 --> 15:34.411
AFTER YOU.AFTER YOU.

15:34.455 --> 15:35.935
[ GROANS ]

15:42.245 --> 15:43.420
HUH?

15:43.464 --> 15:44.378
NO STARES OF DISBELIEF,
I BEG YOU.

15:44.421 --> 15:45.988
[ SIGHS ]

15:46.032 --> 15:48.164
I COULDN'T PASS UP AN ALL-ACCESS
PASS TO THE AQUACADE.

15:48.208 --> 15:49.600
IT MAY BE ALL-ACCESS,

15:49.644 --> 15:51.428
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY,
IT'S NOT ALL-INCLUSIVE.

15:51.472 --> 15:53.213
I KNOW, 'CAUSE I CAN'T GO,
BUT I DON'T CARE,

15:53.256 --> 15:55.084
'CAUSE LILY AND VIVIAN
ARE BACK IN THE WATER FOR PAY.

15:55.128 --> 15:58.392
BUT I WANT YOU THERE,
TAKING PHOTOS AND MAKING NOTES

15:58.435 --> 15:59.828
AND THEN
REPORTING BACK TO ME.

15:59.871 --> 16:01.395
IT DOESN'T SEEM FAIR --
LIKE THE REST OF US

16:01.438 --> 16:03.484
ARE ON SPRING BREAK WHILE YOU'RE
STUCK IN DETENTION.

16:03.527 --> 16:05.051
WELL,
THIS DETENTION'S EASIER,

16:05.094 --> 16:07.314
'CAUSE I KNOW THEY'RE SURROUNDED
BY PEOPLE WHO LOVE THEM

16:07.357 --> 16:09.664
IN THIS VERY EMOTIONAL
AND VULNERABLE TIME.

16:09.707 --> 16:12.145
YOU JUST MAKE SURE THAT EMERSON
IS A VIGILANT BODYGUARD

16:12.188 --> 16:13.973
AND STICKS TO THEM
LIKE GLUE.

16:14.016 --> 16:15.061
PADDLE OUT.

16:16.062 --> 16:18.716
[ SURF MUSIC PLAYS ]

16:43.263 --> 16:46.092
DIPPING A TOE
BACK IN OUR OLD MILIEU

16:46.135 --> 16:47.484
AND SOLVING A MURDER --

16:47.528 --> 16:49.573
THE THOUGHT
BRINGS TINGLES.

16:49.617 --> 16:51.662
ALRIGHT, EVERYBODY,
HERE'S YOUR LANE ASSIGNMENTS.

16:51.706 --> 16:53.751
ITTY-BITTY,
YOU'RE HAIR AND MAKEUP.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.710
I WANT YOU TO GET
INTO BLANCHE'S DRESSING ROOM

16:55.753 --> 16:57.233
AND FIND
THAT HOMICIDAL HAIR GEL.

16:57.277 --> 16:59.061
PIE MAKER,
YOU'RE THE DEAL-MAKER,

16:59.105 --> 17:00.758
A.K.A. THE MERMAIDS' AGENT.

17:00.802 --> 17:02.586
STICK TO JIMMY NEPTUNE.

17:02.630 --> 17:05.720
AS TEAM COACH, I'LL SIDLE UP
TO THE AQUADOLLS' MANAGER

17:05.763 --> 17:08.679
AND GRIEVING HUSBAND,
SHANE TRICKLE.

17:08.723 --> 17:10.812
AND AS TEAM HEAVY,
I'LL ALSO MAKE SURE

17:10.855 --> 17:12.379
YOU TWO HAVE
NOTHING TO WORRY ABOUT

17:12.422 --> 17:15.643
EXCEPT SCISSOR-KICKING ASS
AND TAKING NAMES.

17:15.686 --> 17:18.472
Jimmy:
AQUA TROUPE, CIRCLE 'ROUND
FOR AN IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT.

17:18.515 --> 17:21.083
AS TERRIBLE
AS THESE CIRCUMSTANCES ARE,

17:21.127 --> 17:23.520
THEY'VE ALSO BROUGHT US
SOMETHING WONDERFUL --

17:25.000 --> 17:26.871
A PAIR OF LUMINARIES.

17:26.915 --> 17:28.525
EVERYONE,
PUT YOUR FINS TOGETHER

17:28.569 --> 17:31.137
FOR "A NIGHT OF 1,000 BUBBLES'"
NEW HEADLINERS,

17:32.747 --> 17:34.053
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS!

17:39.754 --> 17:41.321
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:41.364 --> 17:43.714
THAT'S BOGUS, NEPTUNE.

17:43.758 --> 17:45.499
WE HAVE A SIGNED...THING.

17:45.542 --> 17:48.502
WHICH I WILL HONOR BY FINDING
A BOFFO NEW ACT FOR CORAL.

17:48.545 --> 17:51.461
DOES ANYBODY EVEN KNOW
WHO THESE TWO ARE?

17:51.505 --> 17:54.073
I MET MY HUSBAND AT
A DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS SHOW.

17:54.116 --> 17:56.075
THEY'RE THE REASON
WE DEVOTE OUR LIVES TO THIS.

17:56.118 --> 17:57.859
WELL, I HAVE PENS
FOR AUTOGRAPHS.

17:57.902 --> 18:01.689
I OUGHT TO PUNCH YOU
IN THE SNOT LOCKER.

18:01.732 --> 18:04.605
Narrator: AS LILY AND VIVIAN'S
STARS BEGAN TO RISE,

18:04.648 --> 18:07.999
OLIVE ENCOUNTERED ANOTHER STAR,
THAT WAS ABOUT TO FALL.

18:14.963 --> 18:16.399
ARE YOU
THE NEW SEA HORSE?

18:16.443 --> 18:17.835
OH!
HEAVENS TO HAMSTRINGS!

18:17.879 --> 18:19.402
NO, I'M SALLY BOOTS.

18:19.446 --> 18:22.275
FLY GIRL TO, UM...
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS.

18:22.318 --> 18:25.016
SNAP BACK, G-STRING!
I LOVE THEM!

18:25.060 --> 18:26.192
OH, I LOVE YOU.

18:26.235 --> 18:27.932
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

18:27.976 --> 18:29.630
OHHHHH!

18:29.673 --> 18:31.893
[ Straining ] MAMA!

18:31.936 --> 18:34.113
[ EXHALES HEAVILY ]
WHO ARE YOU?

18:34.156 --> 18:36.680
SID TANGO.
I OPEN THE SECOND ACT.

18:36.724 --> 18:38.073
WHY AREN'T YOU OUT THERE
WITH THE REST OF THE GROUP?

18:38.117 --> 18:39.857
THEY'RE RELOCATING ME --

18:39.901 --> 18:41.120
OUT BY THE PORT-O-LETS.

18:41.163 --> 18:42.860
OH, SHOOT.

18:42.904 --> 18:45.385
THERE'S ENOUGH ROOM IN THIS
FISHBOWL FOR ALL US FISH.

18:45.428 --> 18:46.951
YOU KNOW WHAT?
THANK YOU.

18:46.995 --> 18:48.344
IF ONLY MORE PEOPLE
AROUND HERE WOULD BE AS

18:48.388 --> 18:49.911
ACCEPTING OF WHO I AM.

18:49.954 --> 18:51.608
PEOPLE AREN'T ACCEPTING?
HERE?

18:51.652 --> 18:54.829
BEING A MAN
IN AQUA-ENTERTAINMENT.

18:54.872 --> 18:57.136
WHICH IS TO SAY
"UNAPPRECIATED AND INVISIBLE."

18:57.179 --> 18:58.485
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY TIMES
JIMMY NEPTUNE PROMISED ME

18:58.528 --> 18:59.964
THE HEADLINER SPOT?

19:00.008 --> 19:01.444
THOUGHT I'D GET IT
AFTER BLANCHE KICKED.

19:01.488 --> 19:02.793
THEN I HEAR
THEY'RE DRAGGING

19:02.837 --> 19:05.013
THE MUSTY MERMAIDS
OUT OF RETIREMENT!

19:05.056 --> 19:07.624
OH, WELL.
SOMEDAY IT'LL BE MY TURN.

19:07.668 --> 19:09.191
UNTIL THEN,
I'LL BE CONTENT

19:09.235 --> 19:12.063
WATCHING OTHERS
GLIMMER AND GLEAM.

19:12.107 --> 19:13.630
Narrator: IRONICALLY,

19:13.674 --> 19:16.807
OLIVE FOUND THOSE SAME WORDS
STARING BACK AT HER

19:16.851 --> 19:19.636
FROM THE VICINITY
OF CORAL'S DRESSING TABLE.

19:19.680 --> 19:20.942
[ GROANS ]

19:21.899 --> 19:23.249
[ SIGHS ]

19:23.292 --> 19:24.902
THINK CORAL WILL MIND
IF I BORROW THIS?

19:24.946 --> 19:26.774
MY GIRLS ARE GONNA NEED
A TOUCH-UP BEFORE SPLASHDOWN.

19:26.817 --> 19:27.818
NICE TO MEET YOU.
BYE.

19:29.733 --> 19:31.605
I COMBED THE DRESSING ROOM
FOR THE MURDER WEAPON --

19:31.648 --> 19:33.520
WELL,
MURDER-WEAPON TRIGGER.

19:33.563 --> 19:35.478
BLANCHE'S BEAUTY AREA
HAD ALREADY BEEN BROOMED,

19:35.522 --> 19:37.567
BUT I DID FIND
CORAL'S HAIR GEL.

19:37.611 --> 19:38.829
IT SMELLS FINE.

19:40.135 --> 19:42.137
NICE WORK, SEA-WEE.

19:42.181 --> 19:44.661
I GOT A GREAT BIG BUCKETFUL
OF NOTHING.

19:44.705 --> 19:46.707
STILL, YOUR FIND
DOES PROVE OUR THEORY --

19:46.750 --> 19:48.361
BLANCHE WAS DEFINITELY
THE TARGET.

19:48.404 --> 19:49.753
MM-HMM.

19:49.797 --> 19:51.451
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

19:54.018 --> 19:56.847
HOLY IBIZA, MONACO,
AND SAINT-TROPEZ.

19:56.891 --> 19:59.502
THAT IS SOME BANANA HAMMOCK.THAT'S SID TANGO.

19:59.546 --> 20:01.504
I FOUND HIM HANGING
IN BLANCHE'S DRESSING ROOM.

20:01.548 --> 20:03.941
HE'S SORT OF FUN
AND JUST A TEENSY BIT ANGRY

20:03.985 --> 20:06.466
HE WAS OVERLOOKED TO LEAD
THE AQUACADE DUE TO HIS --

20:06.509 --> 20:08.468
WELL, BECAUSE OF...

20:08.511 --> 20:10.165
WHAT'S IN
HIS BANANA HAMMOCK.

20:10.209 --> 20:12.254
I REALLY SHOULD LOOK AWAY,
BUT I-I-I CAN'T.

20:12.298 --> 20:13.864
WANT TO GO BLIND?

20:13.908 --> 20:16.258
I WANT TO CATCH A KILLER.
LOOK AT THE SHARK PEN.

20:16.302 --> 20:18.304
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

20:18.347 --> 20:19.827
SEE THAT?UH-HUH.

20:19.870 --> 20:22.482
IT HAPPENS EVERY TIME
SID TOUCHES HIS BELT.

20:22.525 --> 20:25.354
[ BEEP ]
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

20:25.398 --> 20:27.269
[ BEEP ]
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

20:27.313 --> 20:29.184
[ BEEP, BEEP ]
[ MOTOR WHIRRING ]

20:29.228 --> 20:30.490
COME ON.

20:33.275 --> 20:34.537
EXCUSE ME,
THIS IS WHERE I DIVE.

20:34.581 --> 20:36.539
OH, YOU ABOUT TO BELLY-FLOP,
ALRIGHT.

20:37.888 --> 20:39.716
[ BOING! ]
[ MOTOR WHIRS ]

20:39.760 --> 20:43.285
RIGHT INTO A LITTLE CESSPOOL
I LIKE TO CALL THE COUNTY PEN.

20:43.329 --> 20:45.113
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:45.983 --> 20:47.420
[ BEEP ]

20:50.118 --> 20:51.554
[ BUZZER,
CELL DOORS SLAM ]

20:52.947 --> 20:54.296
WHAT YOU WANT, TANGO?

20:54.340 --> 20:55.297
YOU.

20:55.341 --> 20:56.472
TO GET ME
OUT OF HERE.

20:56.516 --> 20:58.300
LIFE ON THE INSIDE
ROUGH?

20:58.344 --> 20:59.954
I'LL CALL IN A FAVOR
TO THE WARDEN.

20:59.997 --> 21:02.130
MAYBE HE CAN EASE UP
A LITTLE.

21:02.173 --> 21:03.740
WHAT?
HE'S A REGULAR.

21:03.784 --> 21:06.003
SOMETIMES I SERVE HIS PECAN PIE
WITH AN EXTRA SCOOP

21:06.047 --> 21:07.527
OF CARAMEL SAUCE,
COMPLIMENTARY-LIKE.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.050
THIS WAS A FRAME JOB.

21:09.093 --> 21:11.139
I HAD NOTHING TO DO
WITH KILLING BLANCHE.

21:11.182 --> 21:13.750
WHY WOULD I KEEP
THE MURDER WEAPON IN MY SPEEDO?

21:13.794 --> 21:15.665
WHY DON'T YOU SAVE THE
"I DIDN'T DO IT" DANCE

21:15.709 --> 21:17.101
FOR THE JUDGE, TANGO?

21:17.145 --> 21:19.669
YOU HAD OPPORTUNITY,
AND YOU HAD MOTIVE.

21:19.713 --> 21:21.062
YOU ALREADY TOLD ME
THAT YOU WERE JEALOUS

21:21.105 --> 21:22.890
OF THE AQUADOLLS'
HEADLINER SPOT.

21:22.933 --> 21:25.153
MY JEALOUSY
HAS NOTHING TO DO WITH THEM.

21:25.196 --> 21:27.764
IT STEMS FROM LOVING AN ART FORM
THAT DOESN'T LOVE ME BACK.

21:27.808 --> 21:29.940
WHY AREN'T YOU SHINING
YOUR SPOTLIGHT ON CORAL?

21:29.984 --> 21:31.202
IT'S WHAT SHE'S WANTED
ALL HER LIFE.

21:31.246 --> 21:32.465
KEEP SPLASHING.

21:32.508 --> 21:34.336
THERE MAY HAVE BEEN
TWO AQUADOLLS,

21:34.380 --> 21:36.033
BUT IT WAS REALLY
"THE BLANCHE SHOW."

21:36.077 --> 21:37.426
SHE ALWAYS
PUT HERSELF FIRST.

21:37.470 --> 21:39.080
CORAL HATED HER FOR IT.

21:39.123 --> 21:40.864
YOU THINKING LITTLE SISSY
GOT TIRED OF LIVING

21:40.908 --> 21:42.866
IN BIG SISSY'S SHADOW
AND ENGINEERED THE ATTACK?

21:42.910 --> 21:45.652
CORAL DID LAUNCH BLANCHE INTO
THE DIRECTION OF THAT SHARK.

21:45.695 --> 21:46.914
IT'S CERTAINLY A THING
TO MAKE YOU GO...

21:46.957 --> 21:48.481
HMMMM.HMMMM.

21:48.524 --> 21:51.397
Narrator: AS EMERSON COD
LET SID TANGO OFF THE HOOK,

21:51.440 --> 21:53.486
THE PRIVATE DETECTIVE'S
SUSPICIONS

21:53.529 --> 21:55.575
SIDESTROKED
BACK TO THE AQUACADE.

21:57.228 --> 21:58.317
WHAT'S THE MATTER
WITH YOU?

21:58.360 --> 22:00.884
I'M IN MOURNING,
YOU ASS!

22:00.928 --> 22:02.451
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TAKE THAT TRIDENT

22:02.495 --> 22:04.061
AND STAB ME
IN THE HEART?!

22:04.105 --> 22:05.802
PACK YOUR SPANDEX!
YOU'RE FIRED!

22:05.846 --> 22:07.064
WHOA!

22:07.108 --> 22:09.545
EVERYBODY, CHILLAX.
I CAN FIX THIS.

22:09.589 --> 22:10.938
SAVE IT,
SAND FOR BRAINS.

22:10.981 --> 22:12.505
YOU'RE AS USELESS
AS TEATS ON A BOAR.

22:13.897 --> 22:15.551
"TEATS."
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:15.595 --> 22:16.900
CORAL, WAIT!

22:19.425 --> 22:21.731
CAN YOU BELIEVE THE CLAWS
ON THAT SEA MONSTER --

22:21.775 --> 22:23.167
TRYING TO PINCH
MY AQUACADE

22:23.211 --> 22:24.995
AND TURN IT INTO A VEHICLE
FOR HERSELF?!

22:25.039 --> 22:26.257
TALENT --
THEY'RE LIKE CHILDREN.

22:26.301 --> 22:27.650
YOU KNOW
WHAT SHE TRIED TO PITCH?

22:27.694 --> 22:30.000
A ONE-WOMAN TRIBUTE
TO "A CHORUS LINE."

22:30.044 --> 22:31.393
DON'T YOU NEED
A CHORUS AND A LINE?

22:31.437 --> 22:33.047
SHE FIGURED OUT
A WAY AROUND IT!

22:33.090 --> 22:35.702
THE LAST THING I NEED
IS ANOTHER WATER DANCER.

22:35.745 --> 22:37.268
WITH GALVESTON GUS GONE,

22:37.312 --> 22:39.575
THE AUDIENCE IS THIRSTING
FOR A DAREDEVIL ACT.

22:40.750 --> 22:42.012
PICTURE THIS.

22:42.056 --> 22:44.232
A MOTORCYCLE,
BUT IT'S ON FIRE.

22:44.275 --> 22:47.017
AND THERE'S A RAMP,
20 FEET HIGH, ON FIRE, TOO.

22:47.061 --> 22:48.323
A RIDER APPEARS...

22:48.367 --> 22:50.238
ALSO ON FIRE?BETTER -- IN CHAINS.

22:50.281 --> 22:52.327
SHE GUNS THE ENGINE,
SOARS OFF THE RAMP,

22:52.371 --> 22:54.024
THROUGH A HOOP --

22:54.068 --> 22:55.809
MAYBE FLAMING, MAYBE NOT.
I'LL HAVE TO CRUNCH THE NUMBERS.

22:55.852 --> 22:57.419
...AND THEN LANDS
ON THE OTHER SIDE OF THE POOL.

22:57.463 --> 22:59.247
"SHE"?YES -- CORAL!

22:59.290 --> 23:01.467
OR, AT LEAST, IT WAS SUPPOSED
TO BE HER UNTIL I CANNED HER.

23:01.510 --> 23:02.946
STILL, DON'T YOU THINK

23:02.990 --> 23:04.905
THAT'S AN ACT
THAT'LL PUT BUTTS IN SEATS?

23:04.948 --> 23:08.125
ABSOLUTELY. AND I'VE GOT ANOTHER
ACT THAT BUTTS ABSOLUTELY LOVE.

23:08.169 --> 23:09.823
OF COURSE --
THE DARLINGS' CONTRACT.

23:09.866 --> 23:11.564
THERE'S A COUPLE STICKING POINTS
BUT NOTHING TSUNAMI-SIZED.

23:11.607 --> 23:13.392
WHATEVER THEY WANT.REALLY?

23:13.435 --> 23:14.784
BECAUSE I CAME UP WITH A BUNCH
OF STUFF THEY DON'T REALLY NEED,

23:14.828 --> 23:16.395
WANTED TO SEE
IF WE COULD GET AWAY WITH.

23:16.438 --> 23:18.614
THE CHARLES SISTERS
ARE AS EASY AS A LAZY RIVER.

23:18.658 --> 23:20.747
IT'D BE MY PLEASURE
TO HAVE THEM ABOARD.

23:20.790 --> 23:21.922
ON ONE CONDITION.

23:24.403 --> 23:26.709
GREAT NEWS -- JIMMY AGREED
TO ALL OF YOUR DEMANDS.

23:26.753 --> 23:28.537
THE FRESH LILACS?
THE EGYPTIAN-COTTON TOWELS?

23:28.581 --> 23:29.973
THE VODKA FOUNTAIN?

23:30.017 --> 23:31.801
ALL IN THERE. THE PAPERS
WILL BE READY TOMORROW.

23:31.845 --> 23:34.456
BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,
IT ALL HINGES ON ONE THING.

23:34.500 --> 23:37.067
JIMMY'S GONNA TAKE THE AQUACADE
ON A EUROPEAN TOUR.

23:37.111 --> 23:38.329
SIGNING MEANS YOU'LL GO.

23:38.373 --> 23:39.722
OH, EUROPE'S
OUT OF THE QUESTION.

23:39.766 --> 23:41.115
WHO WOULD TAKE CARE
OF THE BIRDS,

23:41.158 --> 23:42.595
PLACE FLOWERS
ON CHARLOTTE'S GRAVE?

23:42.638 --> 23:43.726
AND BESIDES...

23:45.162 --> 23:47.164
LILY HAS
INDULGED ME ENOUGH.

23:47.208 --> 23:48.731
SO OUR ANSWER IS...

23:48.775 --> 23:51.081
YES.

23:51.125 --> 23:54.737
WELL, FOR THE FIRST TIME
SINCE CHARLOTTE DIED,

23:54.781 --> 23:57.697
MAYBE IT'S OKAY
TO LEAVE SADNESS BEHIND

23:57.740 --> 23:59.394
AND...START PUTTING
OUR HAPPINESS FIRST.

24:01.091 --> 24:02.266
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

24:02.310 --> 24:04.791
I THINK CHUCK --
CHARLOTTE --

24:04.834 --> 24:07.533
AS YOU DESCRIBED HER,
WAS A WONDERFUL, CARING WOMAN.

24:07.576 --> 24:09.143
AND SHE, LIKE ME,

24:09.186 --> 24:10.710
WOULD WANT YOU TO PUT
YOUR HAPPINESS FIRST, TOO.

24:10.753 --> 24:12.755
SO I THINK
WE'RE ALL IN AGREEMENT

24:12.799 --> 24:15.279
WHEN I SAY...
SWIM ON, MERMAIDS.

24:15.323 --> 24:17.020
[ WATER BUBBLING ]

24:17.064 --> 24:18.631
OH, MY!
IT'S CORAL!

24:18.674 --> 24:19.632
OH!

24:21.938 --> 24:24.811
EVERYBODY, STAND BACK!
I WAS A LIFEGUARD.

24:24.854 --> 24:26.377
[ GASPS ]
WAS SHE ATTACKED?!

24:26.421 --> 24:28.292
WE SAW THE WHOLE THING --
SHE CHAINED HERSELF UP,

24:28.336 --> 24:29.642
HOPPED ON THE CHOPPER,

24:29.685 --> 24:31.121
AND RODE IT
LIKE A HELLS ANGEL IN DRAG

24:31.165 --> 24:32.558
TILL SHE FELL IN THERE.

24:32.601 --> 24:34.081
WOULD HAVE BEEN FUNNY
IF IT WASN'T SO TRAGIC.

24:34.124 --> 24:35.778
[ COUGHING ]

24:35.822 --> 24:38.128
CORAL! WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU DOING?!

24:38.955 --> 24:40.130
JIMMY?

24:40.174 --> 24:41.305
IS THAT YOU, JIMMY?

24:41.349 --> 24:42.742
All: YES!

24:42.785 --> 24:44.918
I WAS TRYING TO SHOW YOU
THAT I COULD DO IT --

24:44.961 --> 24:47.094
THAT DAREDEVIL ACT
THAT YOU WANTED.

24:47.137 --> 24:49.923
I WILL DO ANYTHING IF IT MEANS
GETTING BACK INTO THE SHOW.

24:49.966 --> 24:51.141
IS THAT SO WRONG?!

24:51.185 --> 24:53.796
NO. BUT LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT IS --

24:53.840 --> 24:55.885
YOUR BROTHER-IN-LAW/MANAGER'S
HANDS

24:55.929 --> 24:58.975
ALL OVER
YOUR PERKY/HEAVING BOOBS.

24:59.019 --> 25:01.021
THIS IS A CERTIFIED
LIFESAVING POSITION.

25:01.064 --> 25:03.589
GET OFF ME, YOU IDIOT!
I TOLD YOU WE WERE THROUGH!

25:03.632 --> 25:05.373
FOR SHAME!

25:05.416 --> 25:07.767
YOU'VE BEEN DOING THE SKINNY-DIP
WITH YOUR SISTER'S HUSBAND!

25:07.810 --> 25:10.509
Narrator:
AT THAT MOMENT,
LILY CHARLES HAD SOMETHING

25:10.552 --> 25:12.685
IN COMMON
WITH A LIFELONG ENEMY.

25:12.728 --> 25:14.556
BOTH WERE ADULTERESSES.

25:14.600 --> 25:17.516
BOTH HAD STOLEN MEN
THEIR SISTERS LOVED.

25:17.559 --> 25:18.865
BOTH WERE...

25:18.908 --> 25:20.214
DISGUSTING.

25:20.257 --> 25:21.955
YOU PUT THE "EVIL"
IN KNIEVEL, LADY.

25:21.998 --> 25:24.174
I GUESS THE SPOTLIGHT
WASN'T THE ONLY THING

25:24.218 --> 25:25.567
YOU DIDN'T WANT TO SHARE
WITH BLANCHE.

25:25.611 --> 25:27.743
YOU JUST WANTED TRICKLE'S PICKLE
TO YOURSELF,

25:27.787 --> 25:29.397
SO YOU FED HER
TO THE SHARKS.

25:29.440 --> 25:31.617
ALRIGHT, ALRIGHT.
I-I ADMIT THAT I-I SLEPT

25:31.660 --> 25:33.967
WITH SHANE
TO SPITE MY SISTER.

25:34.010 --> 25:35.185
BUT I DIDN'T KILL HER.

25:35.229 --> 25:36.622
[ Voice breaking ]
I LOVED HER.

25:36.665 --> 25:39.407
AND NOW SHE'S GONE.
AND WHERE DO I TURN?

25:41.191 --> 25:43.193
TO US.

25:43.237 --> 25:45.500
CORAL, YOU WILL SWIM
WITH OUR ACT TONIGHT.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.154
WHAT?!

25:47.197 --> 25:50.200
IN THE PAST, WHENEVER
I WAS INCAPACITATED BY GRIEF,

25:50.244 --> 25:52.420
GETTING BACK IN THE WATER
WAS THE BEST CURE.

25:52.463 --> 25:53.813
IT WILL HEAL YOU.

25:53.856 --> 25:56.772
ISN'T THAT RIGHT, LILY?REALLY?

25:56.816 --> 25:59.558
THINK SHE'S TELLING
THE TRUTH, COD?

25:59.601 --> 26:01.864
YEAH. TOO BAD, TOO, 'CAUSE
THE JEALOUS,

26:01.908 --> 26:03.126
CRAZY LADY
THAT KILLS HER SISTER

26:03.170 --> 26:04.737
TO BE WITH
THE HIMBO BROTHER-IN-LAW

26:04.780 --> 26:08.131
IS ALWAYS A WELCOME REST STOP
ON THE MOTIVE TURNPIKE.

26:08.175 --> 26:09.480
MAYBE THE REST STOP'S
THE SAME --

26:09.524 --> 26:10.917
JUST ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE ROAD.

26:10.960 --> 26:13.223
AS IN...
THE HIMBO DID IT.

26:13.267 --> 26:14.616
[ MOTORCYCLE REVVING ]

26:14.660 --> 26:15.835
WAIT.
WHERE'S THE HIMBO?

26:17.401 --> 26:19.490
THE HIMBO --
GETTING AWAY WITH MURDER!

26:19.534 --> 26:21.405
HASTA, BIATCHES!

26:28.412 --> 26:29.588
POLICE SEARCHED
SHANE'S VAN.

26:29.631 --> 26:31.677
THEY FOUND
THE LARD-LACED HAIR GEL

26:31.720 --> 26:34.331
AND SOME REALLY SPECIFIC
INSTRUCTIONS

26:34.375 --> 26:36.551
ON HOW TO CLONE
A REMOTE-CONTROLLED GATE OPENER.

26:36.595 --> 26:38.292
THE A.P.B.'s ALREADY OUT.

26:38.335 --> 26:40.381
AND HOW ARE LILY AND VIVIAN
TAKING ALL THIS EXCITEMENT?

26:40.424 --> 26:42.731
VERY WELL.
NOW FOR THE BIG NEWS.

26:42.775 --> 26:46.561
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS
HAVE PICKED UP A THIRD.

26:46.605 --> 26:47.649
[ GASPS ]

26:47.693 --> 26:49.259
WHA-A-A-A-A-A-T?

26:49.303 --> 26:51.392
THAT WAS FAKE SURPRISE.YEAH, IT WAS.

26:51.435 --> 26:54.003
OLIVE'S BEEN KEEPING ME INFORMED
ON ALL THINGS CHARLES SISTERS.

26:54.047 --> 26:55.265
HOW ARE THEY ALL
GETTING ALONG?

26:55.309 --> 26:57.006
VIVIAN IS
HER USUAL SWEET SELF,

26:57.050 --> 26:59.792
LILY SEEMS CAUTIOUS
BUT STILL PROFESSIONAL,

26:59.835 --> 27:01.445
AND CORAL
IS THRILLED TO HAVE A JOB

27:01.489 --> 27:03.926
THAT DOESN'T REQUIRE
A FLAME-RETARDANT ONE-PIECE.

27:03.970 --> 27:05.667
THAT IS JUST GREAT.

27:05.711 --> 27:07.930
NOW, PLEASE, PLEASE,
CAN I OPEN MY BOX?

27:07.974 --> 27:09.279
I'VE BEEN WAITING
ALL DAY.

27:09.323 --> 27:11.194
MY SECOND-ATTEMPT
HALF-BIRTHDAY GIFT

27:11.238 --> 27:12.805
FOR YOU TO WEAR
TOMORROW NIGHT.

27:12.848 --> 27:13.806
I GOT US FRONT-ROW SEATS.

27:13.849 --> 27:15.068
THANK YOU.

27:15.111 --> 27:16.896
[ GASPS ]
NED!

27:16.939 --> 27:20.508
KILLER TICKETS
AND A TOP-NOTCH TAM.

27:20.551 --> 27:21.901
AW, THANK YOU.

27:21.944 --> 27:24.294
IT'S THE, UH,
DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS'

27:24.338 --> 27:25.905
FIRST PROFESSIONAL APPEARANCE
IN YEARS.

27:25.948 --> 27:28.690
THERE'S NO WAY YOU CAN MISS IT,
ESPECIALLY NOW.

27:28.734 --> 27:31.519
AND HERE'S
THE REALLY JUICY SECRET

27:31.562 --> 27:33.913
THAT NOT EVEN OLIVE SNOOK,
THE SPY, KNOWS --

27:33.956 --> 27:35.523
THE AQUACADE
IS HITTING THE ROAD,

27:35.566 --> 27:36.959
AND LILY AND VIVIAN
ARE GOING WITH IT.

27:37.003 --> 27:38.787
"ROAD"?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "ROAD"?

27:38.831 --> 27:42.617
A BUNCH OF THEM, REALLY. UH,
DOWNING STREET, THE AUTOBAHN,

27:42.661 --> 27:45.315
THE CHAMPS-ELYSEES.

27:45.359 --> 27:47.883
BUT THEY'RE EUROPEAN,
AS IN...IN EUROPE.

27:47.927 --> 27:49.015
THAT'S RIGHT.

27:50.625 --> 27:52.845
UH, I DIDN'T EXPECT
FAKE SURPRISE,

27:52.888 --> 27:55.195
BUT I DIDN'T EXPECT
STUNNED SILENCE, EITHER.

27:59.721 --> 28:01.201
HOW COULD YOU
LET THIS HAPPEN?

28:01.244 --> 28:03.986
I DID WHAT YOU TOLD ME.
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE HAPPY.

28:04.030 --> 28:05.945
NED,
THEY THINK I'M DEAD.

28:05.988 --> 28:07.729
THE ONLY WAY
THIS HAS BEEN BEARABLE

28:07.773 --> 28:09.470
IS BECAUSE AT LEAST I'VE BEEN
ABLE TO KEEP TABS ON THEM.

28:09.513 --> 28:10.776
IF THEY NEEDED SOMETHING,

28:10.819 --> 28:12.734
I COULD HELP THEM
OR TRY AND FIX IT,

28:12.778 --> 28:13.909
AND WHILE
I'M COMPLETELY REMOVED,

28:13.953 --> 28:15.737
I'M STILL
PART OF THEIR LIVES.

28:15.781 --> 28:17.913
AND HOW CAN I BE PART OF THEIR
LIVES IF THEY'RE IN EUROPE?!

28:19.262 --> 28:20.394
[ SIGHS ]

28:21.395 --> 28:22.831
THIS IS A GAME-CHANGER.

28:22.875 --> 28:24.485
WHAT GAME?
THIS IS NOT A GAME.

28:24.528 --> 28:27.183
NO, IT'S NOT A GAME.
IT'S MY LIFE.

28:27.227 --> 28:29.577
AND NOW YOU DECIDED
TO MODIFY THE RULES.

28:29.620 --> 28:32.188
I'VE GOT TO RE-EVALUATE WHICH
ONES ACTUALLY KEEP ME HERE.

28:39.108 --> 28:42.764
I'LL JUST SIT HERE AND TRY TO
CONCENTRATE ON NOT THROWING UP.

28:42.808 --> 28:44.679
BUTTERFLIES
MAKING YOU QUEASY?

28:44.723 --> 28:47.334
WHAT SAY WE DROWN THEM WITH A
DIP IN THE VODKA FOUNTAIN?

28:47.377 --> 28:49.510
I NEVER DRINK AND DIVE.

28:49.553 --> 28:51.599
IT'S DISRESPECTFUL
TO THE AUDIENCE.

28:51.642 --> 28:52.948
MORE IMPORTANTLY,
TO VIVIAN.

28:54.210 --> 28:55.429
WHERE IS SHE?

28:55.472 --> 28:57.387
UH, MEETING
WITH THE SOUND TECH.

28:57.431 --> 29:01.174
THE UNDERWATER SPEAKERS
SOUNDED MUDDY IN REHEARSAL.

29:01.217 --> 29:03.698
WELL, LET'S HOPE THEY SOLVE IT
BY SHOWTIME.

29:03.742 --> 29:06.919
Narrator: CORAL HAD SLEPT
WITH HER OWN SISTER'S HUSBAND.

29:06.962 --> 29:10.096
LILY HAD DONE THE SAME
WITH HER SISTER'S FIANCE.

29:10.139 --> 29:11.750
THE SYMMETRY MADE HER FEEL

29:11.793 --> 29:14.665
AS IF SHE WERE LOOKING
AT A REFLECTION OF HERSELF.

29:14.709 --> 29:17.930
AND SINCE "HERSELF"
WAS WHAT SHE HATED MOST,

29:17.973 --> 29:19.932
SHE REJECTED THE MIRROR.

29:19.975 --> 29:23.457
SAY, WHAT IS OUR CHOREOGRAPHY
AT MEASURE 120 AGAIN?

29:23.500 --> 29:26.460
ARE WE REVERSE-CRANING
INTO A BALLET LEG THRUST?

29:26.503 --> 29:27.983
FULL CORKSCREW FIRST.

29:28.027 --> 29:30.203
I THOUGHT
THE CORKSCREW CAME LAST.

29:30.246 --> 29:31.770
OH. HOLD IT.

29:31.813 --> 29:34.294
THAT'S RIGHT --
WHICH MAKES YOU WRONG.

29:34.337 --> 29:35.730
THE CORKSCREW COMES LAST.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.079
YOU'RE LOSING IT, LIL.

29:37.123 --> 29:38.298
I THINK I'LL HAVE THAT NIP,
AFTER ALL.

29:38.341 --> 29:39.690
ARE YOU SURE?

29:39.734 --> 29:41.910
HEY, SHORT ROUND,
LITTLE HELP WITH MY BUN?

29:46.306 --> 29:48.874
OH. YOU'VE GOT
SOMETHING POKING OUT.

29:48.917 --> 29:50.571
LEAVE IT.

29:50.614 --> 29:53.139
SORRY, BUT WHEN I SEE
A STRING, I JUST --

29:55.228 --> 29:56.795
I HAVE TO YANK IT!

29:56.838 --> 29:57.883
HEY!

29:57.926 --> 30:00.146
OH! HOLY GOLD LAME!

30:01.887 --> 30:04.411
YOU'RE TRYING TO BE
A SINGULAR SENSATION.

30:04.454 --> 30:06.239
YOU SWAM YOUR WAY
BACK TO THE AQUACADE

30:06.282 --> 30:07.980
BY PREYING
ON VIVIAN'S SYMPATHY,

30:08.023 --> 30:09.024
ONLY TO TRY
TO BREAK UP THE DARLINGS

30:09.068 --> 30:10.634
BY STAGE-FRIGHTENING LILY

30:10.678 --> 30:13.986
SO YOU CAN RULE THE POOL
IN A ONE-WOMAN CHORUS LINE.

30:14.029 --> 30:15.814
WHERE'S THE TOP HAT?
I'M GONNA SHOVE IT UP YOUR --

30:15.857 --> 30:17.206
OLIVE.

30:17.250 --> 30:18.512
EXCUSE US.

30:24.083 --> 30:27.042
DID YOU KNOW MY SISTER WAS BORN
WITH A HOLE IN HER HEART?

30:27.086 --> 30:28.217
HMM?

30:28.261 --> 30:30.916
THE DOCTORS FIXED IT,
BUT...

30:30.959 --> 30:34.180
SOMETIMES IT LEAKS A BIT
AND...STUFF GETS THROUGH.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.009
STUFF LIKE YOU.

30:37.052 --> 30:38.575
VIVIAN MAY THINK

30:38.619 --> 30:40.751
THAT A WOMAN WHO SLEEPS
WITH HER SISTER'S HUSBAND

30:40.795 --> 30:42.884
DESERVES A SECOND CHANCE,
BUT I DON'T.

30:42.928 --> 30:45.626
YOU'LL ALWAYS BE
WHAT YOU ARE --

30:45.669 --> 30:48.759
A SELFISH,
CONNIVING WRETCH.

30:48.803 --> 30:50.936
THE DARLING MERMAID
DARLINGS

30:50.979 --> 30:54.026
ARE A TEAM
THAT PUTS EACH OTHER FIRST.

30:54.069 --> 30:59.422
SO GET IN YOUR SHOWBOAT
AND ROW IT TO HELL.

30:59.466 --> 31:02.295
THIS, UH, "PUTTING OTHERS FIRST"
THAT YOU'RE SO PROUD OF --

31:02.338 --> 31:04.993
I ASSUME IT DIDN'T APPLY
TO YOUR BABY.

31:06.952 --> 31:07.996
I NEVER HAD A BABY.

31:08.040 --> 31:09.302
HMM.
THAT'S WHAT VIVIAN SAID.

31:09.345 --> 31:11.478
YEAH, WE WERE
JUST MAKING SMALL TALK,

31:11.521 --> 31:14.307
AND I CASUALLY ASKED HER
IF YOU HAD A SON OR A DAUGHTER,

31:14.350 --> 31:17.397
AND SHE TOLD ME THAT
NEITHER OF YOU HAD ANY CHILDREN.

31:17.440 --> 31:19.442
ISN'T THAT STRANGE?

31:19.486 --> 31:21.140
WORLD'S FULL OF SPINSTERS.

31:21.183 --> 31:22.793
YOU KNOW, 30 YEARS AGO,

31:22.837 --> 31:26.667
YOU AND I CHANGED
NEXT TO EACH OTHER AFTER A SHOW,

31:26.710 --> 31:29.931
AND THE SEAMSTRESS
HAD TO LET OUT YOUR COSTUME,

31:29.975 --> 31:31.324
THE FLIPPERS
DIDN'T FIT YOUR FEET,

31:31.367 --> 31:34.370
AND YOU HAD THAT
JUST-KNOCKED-UP GLOW ABOUT YOU.

31:35.719 --> 31:37.286
AND THEN YOU DISAPPEARED
FOR NINE MONTHS.

31:37.330 --> 31:39.723
HMM.

31:39.767 --> 31:43.075
SO, WHERE'S THE KID...
SPINSTER?

31:43.118 --> 31:45.033
AND WHY ARE YOU HIDING IT
FROM VIVIAN?

31:45.077 --> 31:47.557
BREATHE ANOTHER WORD,
AND IT'LL BE YOUR LAST.

31:47.601 --> 31:48.602
NOW GET OUT!

31:48.645 --> 31:49.951
YOU'LL REGRET THIS.

31:57.437 --> 31:59.091
CORAL HAD TO CANCEL.
SHE'S SICK.

31:59.134 --> 32:00.353
THEN IT'S JUST US.

32:01.745 --> 32:04.052
AS IT REALLY SHOULD BE,
I SUPPOSE.

32:04.096 --> 32:05.445
READY?

32:05.488 --> 32:06.837
I CAN'T.

32:06.881 --> 32:08.100
LILY...

32:08.143 --> 32:11.320
WE'VE COME THIS FAR.

32:11.364 --> 32:13.540
THIS TIME,
DON'T DO IT FOR ME.

32:15.368 --> 32:16.978
DO IT FOR YOU.

32:17.022 --> 32:18.240
HMM?

32:21.940 --> 32:24.290
Narrator: MEANWHILE,
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS'

32:24.333 --> 32:28.163
ONE-MAN SECURITY DETAIL
SPIED A LURKING SHADOW.

32:32.211 --> 32:34.126
OH, HELL YEAH.

32:34.169 --> 32:37.390
Narrator:
WHICH CALLED TO MIND
A MURDEROUS SURFER NAMED SHANE.

32:37.433 --> 32:39.131
TRICKLE, DOWN!
ON THE GROUND!

32:39.174 --> 32:42.395
DEAD GIRL? DON'T YOU KNOW
THERE'S A KILLER ON THE LOOSE?

32:42.438 --> 32:44.614
HEY!
THINK AGAIN, FOOL!

32:44.658 --> 32:46.573
NOW STEP OUT
WITH YOUR HANDS UP.

32:55.930 --> 32:57.236
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

32:57.279 --> 32:59.064
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?I ASKED YOU FIRST.

32:59.107 --> 33:00.761
THE PERSON WHO'S SNEAKING
AROUND IN THE DARK

33:00.804 --> 33:02.371
WEARING THE DAMN DISGUISE

33:02.415 --> 33:04.808
IS USUALLY THE PERSON
WITH THE MOST EXPLAINING TO DO.

33:07.594 --> 33:09.291
THAT'D BE YOU,
DEAD GIRL.

33:09.335 --> 33:11.076
WELL,
I CAME UP HERE TO --

33:11.119 --> 33:13.687
TO GET A BETTER VANTAGE POINT
OF LILY AND VIVIAN SWIMMING.

33:13.730 --> 33:15.515
THAT'S A LIE.
FROM MY EXCELLENT VANTAGE POINT

33:15.558 --> 33:16.820
IN THE SHADOWS,
I SAW HER TAKE THEIR MUSIC

33:16.864 --> 33:18.170
OUT OF THE CD PLAYER.

33:18.213 --> 33:19.649
I DID NOT.
LOOK -- IT'S STILL IN HERE.

33:19.693 --> 33:21.912
LOOK -- SEE?
'CAUSE I PUT IT BACK IN THERE.

33:21.956 --> 33:24.002
AND I FEEL REALLY ASHAMED NOW.
I'M SO SORRY.

33:24.045 --> 33:26.091
YOU'RE ALSO REALLY LOUSY
AT EXPLAINING THINGS,

33:26.134 --> 33:28.049
'CAUSE THE MORE YOU TALK,
THE MORE LOST I GET.

33:28.093 --> 33:29.877
I WAS REALLY HAPPY
FOR LILY AND VIVIAN

33:29.920 --> 33:32.358
UNTIL THEIR HAPPINESS
THREATENED MY HAPPINESS.

33:32.401 --> 33:34.142
SO, IN A MOMENT
OF WEAKNESS AND PANIC,

33:34.186 --> 33:37.058
I SNUCK UP HERE, AND I TRIED
TO SABOTAGE THEIR SHOW

33:37.102 --> 33:38.320
IN THE HOPE
THAT THEY'D STAY.

33:38.364 --> 33:39.713
DESPICABLE.

33:41.062 --> 33:42.933
NOW YOU.

33:42.977 --> 33:44.196
I GUESS
I MUST HAVE THOUGHT

33:44.239 --> 33:46.502
CHUCK WOULD TRY
TO DO SOMETHING RASH.

33:46.546 --> 33:48.548
SO I CAME UP HERE
TO STOP HER.

33:48.591 --> 33:49.897
HERE'S THE PIE HOLE
MELLOW MIX

33:49.940 --> 33:51.812
YOU ASKED ME
TO GET OUT OF MY CAR.

33:51.855 --> 33:54.945
YOU KNOW WHAT I REALIZED ON
MY FULL-TILT RUN BACK UP HERE?

33:54.989 --> 33:57.426
WHOO! FIRST, THERE'S A LOT
OF STEPS IN THIS PLACE.

33:57.470 --> 33:58.862
BUT SECOND, LILY NEVER
MENTIONED THERE

33:58.906 --> 34:00.125
WAS A LAST-MINUTE
MUSIC CHANGE.

34:00.168 --> 34:01.735
THERE WASN'T.

34:01.778 --> 34:04.129
PIE BOY HERE WAS GONNA TORPEDO
THEIR PERFORMANCE.

34:05.304 --> 34:06.566
OH, HOW COULD YOU?!

34:11.266 --> 34:12.833
WHEN CHUCK'S HAPPINESS
WAS THREATENED BY LILY

34:12.876 --> 34:14.487
AND VIVIAN'S HAPPINESS,
MY HAPPINESS FREAKED OUT

34:14.530 --> 34:15.879
BECAUSE I THOUGHT
CHUCK WAS GONNA LEAVE ME

34:15.923 --> 34:17.881
AND FOLLOW THEM TO EUROPE.

34:17.925 --> 34:21.233
YOU KNOW,
I'M A SOLO GUY BY NATURE,

34:21.276 --> 34:24.888
BUT I CHOOSE TO AFFILIATE MYSELF
WITH THE BOTH OF YOU.

34:24.932 --> 34:26.586
REASON BEING
IS BECAUSE

34:26.629 --> 34:29.241
WHEN YOU SPEND ALL YOUR TIME
CHASING BAD GUYS,

34:29.284 --> 34:32.809
YOU WANT THE BEST
OF THE GOOD GUYS IN YOUR CORNER.

34:32.853 --> 34:35.943
YOU TWO, NORMALLY,
ARE AS SOLID AS THEY COME

34:35.986 --> 34:37.292
BECAUSE YOUR MORAL COMPASS

34:37.336 --> 34:41.079
IS ALWAYS POINTED DUE...
"THE RIGHT THING."

34:43.124 --> 34:46.040
BUT CLEARLY,
SOMEONE'S BEEN SCREWING

34:46.084 --> 34:47.650
WITH BOTH OF YOUR
MAGNETIC FIELDS,

34:47.694 --> 34:49.391
'CAUSE THE BOTH OF YOU
SEEM REALLY LOST RIGHT NOW.

34:49.435 --> 34:51.001
SO I'M GONNA HELP YOU OUT

34:51.045 --> 34:54.004
BY PERSONALLY ESCORTING
AND THEN PHYSICALLY EJECTING

34:54.048 --> 34:56.703
BOTH OF YOUR ASSES
FROM THESE PREMISES.

34:56.746 --> 34:58.357
NOW, WHAT YOU THINK
ABOUT THAT?

35:02.317 --> 35:05.451
Narrator:
AT THAT MOMENT,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES' WALK OF SHAME

35:05.494 --> 35:08.193
TURNED INTO TRIUMPH.

35:08.236 --> 35:10.934
[ DANCE VERSION OF TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"WALTZ OF THE FLOWERS" PLAYS ]

35:35.002 --> 35:36.482
Narrator:
THE BEAT OF THEIR HAPPY HEARTS

35:36.525 --> 35:38.701
AND THE BLARE
OF THE UNDERWATER SPEAKERS

35:38.745 --> 35:41.182
DROWNED OUT THE SOUND
OF IMPENDING DOOM.

35:44.446 --> 35:45.926
[ CROWD GASPS ]

35:50.060 --> 35:51.540
CORAL!

35:51.584 --> 35:53.151
I DID IT FOR YOU,
CORAL!

35:53.194 --> 35:55.065
NOBODY ASKED YOU TO,
SHANE!

35:55.109 --> 35:56.545
YOU KNOW WHAT'S GREAT
ABOUT EVERYONE

35:56.589 --> 35:58.156
THINKING THAT YOU'RE STUPID?

35:58.199 --> 35:59.461
THEY ASSUME THAT YOU CAN'T
GET AWAY WITH MURDER.

35:59.505 --> 36:01.202
BUT I DID!

36:01.246 --> 36:04.640
YOU ALSO SENT A SHARK INTO
THE WATER WHILE I WAS SWIMMING!

36:04.684 --> 36:06.294
DID YOU THINK ABOUT THAT,
PROFESSOR?

36:06.338 --> 36:08.862
YES! IT'S WHY
I SMEARED YOUR COSTUME

36:08.905 --> 36:11.560
WITH THE PROTEIN SECRETIONS
OF THE RED SEA MOSES SOLE.

36:11.604 --> 36:12.518
A LITTLE-KNOWN
SHARK REPELLENT.

36:12.561 --> 36:14.128
THAT'S IT.

36:14.172 --> 36:16.522
WHY DON'T YOU JUST DROP
THE MICROPHONE, THERE, TRICKLE?

36:16.565 --> 36:18.176
OH, I-I-I PLAN TO --

36:18.219 --> 36:19.916
IN THE POOL!

36:19.960 --> 36:21.962
BECAUSE THE CORD WILL SHOOT OUT
A CURRENT THROUGH THE WATER

36:22.005 --> 36:24.704
AND ELECTROCUTE
THE DARLING MERMAID DARLINGS!

36:24.747 --> 36:26.923
ONCE LILY AND VIVIAN CHARLES
ARE DEAD,

36:26.967 --> 36:29.709
JIMMY WILL FINALLY HAVE TO
MAKE YOU THE STAR OF THE SHOW.

36:29.752 --> 36:31.406
THAT'S ALL
YOU EVER WANTED.

36:31.450 --> 36:33.365
OH. NOW I GET IT.

36:33.408 --> 36:36.455
LOOK AT ME, CORAL!
IT'S ALL FOR YOU!

36:38.283 --> 36:39.936
SHA-A-A-A-NE!

36:50.382 --> 36:52.514
[ CHEERING ]

37:06.354 --> 37:09.009
Narrator: BUT THE VICTORY
OF THE PREVIOUS NIGHT FADED

37:09.052 --> 37:11.925
IN THE LIGHT OF A CONVERSATION
THAT HAD TO BE HAD.

37:11.968 --> 37:13.753
MORNING.

37:13.796 --> 37:15.145
I HOPE
THAT GIFT'S NOT FOR ME.

37:15.189 --> 37:17.278
MY HALF-BIRTHDAY'S OVER.

37:17.322 --> 37:19.106
THE GIFTS
I GAVE YOU BEFORE

37:19.149 --> 37:21.282
ONLY TRIGGERED
CRISIS AND MISERY.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.805
REALLY?
I HADN'T NOTICED.

37:24.198 --> 37:25.852
GIVE THIS ONE A SHOT?

37:31.118 --> 37:33.163
[ GASPS ]

37:33.207 --> 37:34.513
I DON'T REMEMBER
THIS PICTURE.

37:34.556 --> 37:37.080
I REMEMBER THE DAY,
BUT NOT THE SHOT.

37:37.124 --> 37:39.126
BECAUSE I TOOK IT
WITH MY JUNIOR INSTAMATIC.

37:39.169 --> 37:40.301
IT WAS THE FIRST TIME
I MET YOUR AUNTS.

37:40.345 --> 37:42.782
THEY WERE
BUZZING THROUGH TOWN

37:42.825 --> 37:45.045
ON THE WAY TO SOME
FAR-OFF AND FANTASTIC PLACE.

37:45.088 --> 37:46.829
I HAD ALMOST FORGOTTEN
THOSE AUNTS,

37:46.873 --> 37:50.268
SO...THANK YOU
FOR REMINDING ME.

37:50.311 --> 37:54.184
CHUCK, I TRY VERY HARD
TO BE A GOOD BOYFRIEND.

37:54.228 --> 37:56.839
I BELIEVE THAT, EVERY DAY,
EVEN IN THE SMALLEST WAYS,

37:56.883 --> 37:59.320
I TRY TO PUT YOUR HAPPINESS
BEFORE MY OWN.

37:59.364 --> 38:01.279
YEAH, I AGREE WITH THAT
WHOLE HEARTEDLY.

38:03.324 --> 38:05.326
I'VE BEEN LYING TO YOU.

38:05.370 --> 38:07.067
NOT THAT
IT'S ANY KIND OF EXCUSE,

38:07.110 --> 38:09.504
BUT I THINK IT'S BECAUSE
I'VE BEEN LYING TO MYSELF, TOO.

38:09.548 --> 38:11.898
IF LILY AND VIVIAN
KNEW YOU WERE STILL ALIVE,

38:11.941 --> 38:13.900
THE ONLY PERSON IN DANGER
WOULD BE ME.

38:14.770 --> 38:15.989
[ SIGHS ]

38:16.032 --> 38:17.773
AND THE DANGER ITSELF
IS A LIE.

38:17.817 --> 38:19.253
IT'S IRRATIONAL FEAR
IN DANGER'S CLOTHING,

38:19.297 --> 38:20.820
AND IT'S WHISPERING
IN MY EAR,

38:20.863 --> 38:22.604
SAYING, "CHUCK LOVES
HER MOTHER AND AUNT SO MUCH

38:22.648 --> 38:24.476
"THAT THERE'S NO WAY SHE WOULD
WANT TO SPEND HER LIFE WITH YOU

38:24.519 --> 38:26.739
IF SHE COULD STILL
BE WITH THEM."

38:26.782 --> 38:30.873
AND SO I PUT MY HAPPINESS
FIRST AND...

38:30.917 --> 38:34.355
TOLD EVERYONE THAT NO ONE COULD
KNOW YOU WERE ALIVE AGAIN,

38:34.399 --> 38:36.575
ESPECIALLY
LILY AND VIVIAN CHARLES.

38:36.618 --> 38:38.098
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT YOU WERE DOING.

38:38.141 --> 38:39.317
I DO NOW.

38:40.361 --> 38:41.493
AND NOW...

38:43.625 --> 38:45.975
I'M FINALLY PUTTING
YOUR HAPPINESS BEFORE MY OWN.

38:56.812 --> 39:01.077
Narrator: AT THIS VERY MOMENT,
A LIFE EVENT WAS TAKING PLACE.

39:01.121 --> 39:04.429
LILY CHARLES HAD BEGUN
TO EXPERIENCE FEELINGS

39:04.472 --> 39:05.560
THAT HAD BECOME FOREIGN.

39:05.604 --> 39:07.693
THESE PLEASANT SENSATIONS...

39:07.736 --> 39:10.130
LILY.Narrator:
...WERE NOT TO LAST.

39:10.173 --> 39:11.566
CORAL?

39:15.353 --> 39:20.445
CORAL AND I JUST HAD
AN ILLUMINATING CONVERSATION --

39:20.488 --> 39:22.272
ONE THAT HELPED ME
PUT TOGETHER THE PIECES

39:22.316 --> 39:23.622
OF A 30-YEAR-OLD MYSTERY.

39:26.451 --> 39:29.192
THERE WAS A PART OF ME
THAT ALWAYS KNEW.

39:29.236 --> 39:30.890
BUT I WOULDN'T ALLOW
MYSELF TO ENTERTAIN

39:30.933 --> 39:32.413
SUCH HORRID THOUGHTS --

39:32.457 --> 39:36.374
THAT MY BELOVED SISTER
WOULD GO BEHIND MY BACK

39:36.417 --> 39:39.812
WITH MY FIANCE
AND HAVE A CHILD.

39:41.596 --> 39:43.076
IT WAS CHARLOTTE,
WASN'T IT?

39:46.296 --> 39:49.169
I TRIED THOUSANDS OF TIMES
TO TELL YOU.

39:49.212 --> 39:50.605
BUT I COULDN'T FIND A WAY
TO DO IT.

39:50.649 --> 39:53.347
WHY DO YOU THINK
I HID FROM THE WORLD?

39:53.391 --> 39:56.437
I WAS SO ASHAMED, I COULDN'T
BEAR TO HAVE ANYONE LOOK AT ME.

39:56.481 --> 39:57.656
I UNDERSTAND.

39:57.699 --> 39:59.875
I CAN'T BEAR
TO LOOK AT YOU, EITHER.

39:59.919 --> 40:02.400
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

40:02.443 --> 40:05.577
I TOOK THE LIBERTY
OF CALLING YOU A CAB.

40:05.620 --> 40:07.579
WHERE AM I
SUPPOSED TO GO?

40:07.622 --> 40:09.232
ANYWHERE BUT HERE.

40:12.235 --> 40:14.542
YOU KNOW, I HAVE SPENT
HALF A LIFETIME

40:14.586 --> 40:15.717
TRYING TO MAKE AMENDS.

40:17.502 --> 40:21.419
I GAVE UP THE ONLY MAN
I HAVE EVER LOVED,

40:21.462 --> 40:24.596
[ Voice breaking ] AS WELL AS
MY BEAUTIFUL BABY DAUGHTER,

40:24.639 --> 40:26.989
BECAUSE I KNEW THE TRUTH
WOULD BREAK YOUR HEART.

40:28.643 --> 40:31.472
SO I BROKE MINE INSTEAD.

40:31.516 --> 40:36.042
I DID WHAT I HAVE DONE
SINCE THE DAY YOU WERE BORN --

40:36.085 --> 40:37.652
CHOSE YOUR HAPPINESS
OVER MINE.

40:38.958 --> 40:40.307
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
ANYMORE.

40:41.613 --> 40:42.701
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

40:42.744 --> 40:44.529
[ SCOFFS ]
ALRIGHT!

40:48.837 --> 40:50.404
LILY...

40:50.448 --> 40:52.885
VIVIAN...

40:52.928 --> 40:55.583
Narrator: AT THAT VERY MOMENT,
TIME STOPPED,

40:55.627 --> 40:57.106
AS IT IS WON'T TO DO

40:57.150 --> 41:00.196
WHEN PRESENT, PAST,
AND FUTURE COLLIDE --

41:00.240 --> 41:02.677
WHEN ONE'S EXISTENCE
CEASES TO BE MEASURED

41:02.721 --> 41:04.505
IN DAYS, HOURS, AND MINUTES,

41:04.549 --> 41:09.031
BUT INSTEAD IN THE IMMEASURABLE
QUANTITY OF LIFE EVENTS.

41:09.075 --> 41:11.033
FOR LILY AND VIVIAN CHARLES,

41:11.077 --> 41:14.776
THE REAPPEARANCE OF A DAUGHTER
AND NIECE WAS A LIFE EVENT

41:14.820 --> 41:18.388
THAT WOULD EVENTUALLY OVERSHADOW
A 30-YEAR-OLD BETRAYAL

41:18.432 --> 41:20.695
AND RESULT
IN A SPLASH OF WATER,

41:20.739 --> 41:22.436
THE ROAR OF THE CROWD,

41:22.480 --> 41:26.962
AND A WHIRLWIND TOUR
AROUND THE WORLD -- TWICE.

41:27.006 --> 41:30.618
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR EMERSON COD
WOULD EXPERIENCE A LIFE EVENT

41:30.662 --> 41:33.229
WHEN LIFE FOUND HIM THROUGH
THE PAGES OF A POP-UP BOOK

41:33.273 --> 41:36.537
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
AND HE WAS REUNITED
WITH HIS OWN LIL' GUM SHOE.

41:36.581 --> 41:38.321
Penny:
I'M LOOKING FOR EMERSON COD.

41:46.199 --> 41:49.289
Narrator:
JOCKEY-CUM-WAITRESS-CUM-
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR OLIVE SNOOK

41:49.332 --> 41:52.248
WOULD EXPERIENCE TWO LIFE EVENTS
IN QUICK SUCCESSION --

41:52.292 --> 41:53.902
THE FIRST, OPENING HER HEART

41:53.946 --> 41:56.209
TO A FORMERLY FRIENDLESS
TAXIDERMIST,

41:56.252 --> 41:58.516
AND THE SECOND
BY OPENING A CULINARY PALACE

41:58.559 --> 42:01.040
DEDICATED TO THE ART
OF MACARONI AND CHEESE

42:01.083 --> 42:02.694
CALLED "THE INTREPID COW."

42:04.522 --> 42:07.263
FOR THE PIE MAKER
AND A DEAD GIRL NAMED CHUCK,

42:07.307 --> 42:09.918
THEIR SHARED LIFE EVENT
BEGAN WITH A TOUCH

42:09.962 --> 42:12.399
AND BECAME
THE PROMISE OF NEW FAMILY

42:12.442 --> 42:13.922
BROUGHT ABOUT
BY THE WORDS...

42:13.966 --> 42:15.271
I'M ALIVE.

42:18.710 --> 42:21.669
Narrator: AT THAT MOMENT
IN THE TOWN OF COEUR d'COEURS,

42:21.713 --> 42:24.237
EVENTS OCCURRED
THAT ARE NOT, WERE NOT,

42:24.280 --> 42:27.414
AND SHOULD NEVER BE CONSIDERED
AN ENDING,

42:27.457 --> 42:30.460
FOR ENDINGS, AS IT IS KNOWN,
ARE WHERE WE BEGIN.
